.TH "ssh_ptl_init" 9 "ssh_ptl_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssh_ptl_init \- Initialize packet transport layer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssh_ptl_init
.BI "(struct ssh_ptl *ptl "  ","
.BI "struct serdev_device *serdev "  ","
.BI "struct ssh_ptl_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ptl" 12
The packet transport layer to initialize.
.IP "serdev" 12
The underlying serial device, i.e. the lower-level transport.
.IP "ops" 12
Packet layer operations.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initializes the given packet transport layer. Transmitter and receiver
threads must be started separately via \fBssh_ptl_tx_start\fP and
\fBssh_ptl_rx_start\fP, after the packet-layer has been initialized and the
lower-level transport layer has been set up.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns zero on success and a nonzero error code on failure.
